This article discusses an executive order issued by President Joe Biden to support military-connected families, including military and veteran families, military caregivers, and survivors. The order acknowledges the challenges faced by military families, such as frequent moves, caring for wounded service members, and unemployment of military spouses. The order aims to promote economic opportunity for military spouses and improve access to affordable childcare. It also calls for the development of a strategic plan for hiring and retaining military and veteran spouses in federal jobs, as well as expanding support for military spouse entrepreneurs. The order emphasizes the importance of supporting military families for national security and highlights the need for diversity and inclusion in the federal workforce.